parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the motorcycle to lose power, resulting in accidents or leaving the rider stranded.
symptoms: The ignition switch overheats and fails; the wiring harness melts; the motorcycle loses power and won't start.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the tachometer can cause the motorcycle to stall and quit, resulting in accidents or leaving the rider stranded.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracked wheel hubs can lead to wheel failure, causing loss of control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: Cracks in the front and rear wheel hubs
often discovered during routine maintenance or inspection
with no apparent cause or warning signs.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The cracking and failure of the rear hub can lead to a loss of control, accidents, and potentially fatal injuries, especially if the hub disintegrates while the motorcycle is in motion.
symptoms: Cracks appear on the rear hub
which can worsen over time; the hub may disintegrate
causing the motorcycle to become unstable or lose control.
